==Useful Info==
'''War gargoyles''' are significantly deadlier than any of their [[List of constructs#Gargoyles|gargoyle]] brethren, capable of blasting you with deadly shrapnel. They can be occasionally found in [[the Vaults]] (often with [[peacekeeper]]s), and sometimes found in [[the Iron City of Dis]] and near its [[Vestibule of Hell|entrance]].

{{monster spells}}

==Tips & Tricks==
*Metal Sprinters deals high damage, enough to two-shot many characters entering the Vaults, though it is thrice reduced by [[AC]], and it is subject to a [[Breath]] cooldown.
*War gargoyles can be dangerous alone, but they usually spawn with [[peacekeeper]]s (inflicts [[might]]) and [[crystal golem]]s (another high damage, high AC enemy).
*They are weak to [[Lee's Rapid Deconstruction]].

==History==
*War gargoyles were added in [[0.14]].
